### {100}{}{Stranger.}
{100}{}{陌生人 -- Stranger.}
### {101}{}{Is this a store?}
{101}{}{这是一家商店吗？ -- Is this a store?}
### {102}{}{Yep, and I'd rather keep it that way, grandpa.}
{102}{}{是的，爷爷，我宁愿这样。 -- Yep, and I'd rather keep it that way, grandpa.}
### {103}{}{Well, [he looks around,] very well could be. In fact, I'd be damned if it ain't. Got coins?}
{103}{}{嗯，（他环顾四周）很可能。事实上，如果不是这样，我会被诅咒的。有硬币吗？ -- Well, [he looks around,] very well could be. In fact, I'd be damned if it ain't. Got coins?}
### {104}{}{Yes, let's trade.}
{104}{}{是的，我们交易吧。 -- Yes, let's trade.}
### {105}{}{Yeah, but... I'd better hold onto 'em. Last copper and all. Might get lucky at the slots.}
{105}{}{是的，但是。。。我最好抓住他们。最后的铜和所有。可能在老虎机上运气不错。 -- Yeah, but... I'd better hold onto 'em. Last copper and all. Might get lucky at the slots.}
### {106}{}{Seen you before. Up for trade?}
{106}{}{以前见过你。准备交易吗？ -- Seen you before. Up for trade?}
### {107}{}{Sure.}
{107}{}{当然 -- Sure.}
### {108}{}{Do you ever have something interesting to say?}
{108}{}{你有什么有趣的话要说吗？ -- Do you ever have something interesting to say?}
### {109}{}{I'm still looking.}
{109}{}{我还在找。 -- I'm still looking.}
### {110}{}{Nope.}
{110}{}{没有。 -- Nope.}
### {111}{}{Never mind then, let's trade.}
{111}{}{那没关系，我们交易吧。 -- Never mind then, let's trade.}
### {112}{}{Guess not.}
{112}{}{我猜不会。 -- Guess not.}
### {113}{}{You see: an grumpy old man.}
{113}{}{你看：一个脾气暴躁的老人。 -- You see: an grumpy old man.}
### {114}{}{He's running the shop and is eyeing you with a mixture of suspicion and annoyance.}
{114}{}{他在经营这家商店，怀着怀疑和烦恼的心情盯着你。 -- He's running the shop and is eyeing you with a mixture of suspicion and annoyance.}
### {115}{}{Did you forget something?}
{115}{}{你忘了什么吗？ -- Did you forget something?}
### {116}{}{I see myself out.}
{116}{}{我看到自己出局了。 -- I see myself out.}
